## GetEffectiveSpellPower ‚Äî CombatHero `0x244`

Impl `0x00A6A7E0`. Signature: `int __thiscall(ref, int flag)` ‚Äî **two args, `ret 8`**.

`spellRef` (5 dwords on stack): `+0x00` spell obj (may NULL), `+0x04` spell id (0 = skip school bonuses).

Patch pattern (zeroed spellRef = no spell context):

```asm
xor eax, eax
push eax; push eax; push eax; push eax; push eax   ; 5-dword spellRef
; ecx = CombatHero subobject
push 0
lea eax, [esp+4]
push eax
call dword ptr [edx+0x244]   ; eax = effective spellpower
add esp, 0x14
```

## The `0x164` trap (AdvMap hero)

`0x164` (`0x00B4B3E0`) is `GetSpellPower(spellRef*)` ‚Äî **`ret 4`**, one stack arg. Calling without pushing an arg desyncs the stack and may return fixed `8`. Use `+0x18` for plain total spellpower, or CombatHero `0x244` for combat-buffed value.

